This article summarizes remarks made by President Trump during the signing of the VA Accountability and Whistleblower Protection Act. The President praised the efforts of Secretary Shulkin and the dedication of veterans, highlighting the need to fulfill the duty to them. He criticized the government for failing to keep its promises to veterans and mentioned the VA scandals that occurred in the past. The President emphasized the importance of VA accountability and the protection of whistleblowers, stating that the new law allows the VA Secretary to remove federal employees who fail to provide proper care to veterans. He also mentioned other reforms and actions taken to improve the VA, such as the creation of the Office of Accountability and the launch of a new website that publishes wait times at every VA hospital. The President expressed his commitment to providing world-class care for veterans and signed the VA Accountability and Whistleblower Protection Act into law.